This paper deals with the problem of multiflow routing in networks, which is a topic in computer networks and graph theory. The paper discusses the properties of cut-sufficient pairs and their relationship with series-parallel graphs, which are topics in graph theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). However, the paper also involves combinatorial optimization and graph algorithms, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the characterization of graphs, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
